<br>
This is true, I only mentioned &quot;honor&quot; as one particular virtue that an evil character may be lacking.  Honor and loyalty may very well be attributes possessed by a dark character, but then again, they just as easily may not be.<br>
<br>
I just meant to point out that there may be several reasons, or roleplayed justifications for an evil character attacking their own deity's plane.  Betrayal or personal greed/desire for power is one.  On the flip side of the coin, as many have pointed out, it could be taken as a peculiar form of zealotry, a way of honoring one's god, by daring to hate the Hate god in his presence, fearing the Fear god, battling the War god, killing the Death god.  Somewhat twisted, perhaps, but aren't all &quot;evil&quot; characters inherantly just a bit twisted? :) <p><B><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS">--Tukka</FONT></B><BR>
